∀ {P Q : Prop}, (P → Q) → (Q → P)

elaborated-prompts.theorem:
∀ {m n : ℕ},
  ((¬∃ p, Nat.Prime p ∧ p ∣ m) ∧ ¬∃ q, Nat.Prime q ∧ q ∣ n) ∨ (¬m = n → ∃ p, Nat.Prime p ∧ p ∣ m ∧ p ∣ n) → m = n
elaborated-prompts.prompt: Two natural numbers are equal if and only if they are both divisible by some prime number.
all-elabs: ∀ {m n : ℕ}, (∃ (p : ℕ), Nat.Prime p ∧ p ∣ m ∧ p ∣ n) ↔ m = n
∀ {m n : ℕ}, (¬ (∃ (p : ℕ), Nat.Prime p ∧ p ∣ m) ∧ ¬ (∃ (q : ℕ), Nat.Prime q ∧ q ∣ n)) ∨ (¬(m = n) → (∃ (p : ℕ), Nat.Prime p ∧ p ∣ m ∧ p ∣ n)) → m = n
